ons & University Archives    Finding Aids    Rare Books    Maps & GIS    Digital Images    Using Special Collections & University Archives    Special Collections Research Guides       Eyebrow menu    Contact Us    My Accounts    Give to the Library    COVID-19    UIC menu    UIC.edu    Campus Map    UIC Today     Toggle Search            View Menu       Breadcrumbs    Home    About    Digital Scholarship     Digital Scholarship     About  The Digital Scholarship Hub in the Richard J. Daley Library was developed to provide a greater digital scholarship presence on the UIC campus. Visitors to the Hub can meet with librarians and Digital Humanities Initiative staff members for help with digital humanities, digital scholarship, digital publishing, GIS (geographic information system) and other projects.   Equipment and software available at the Hub include GIS data visualization displays, 3D printers, a sewing machine, computers outfitted with software for data and text mining, scanning and prototyping technologies, and a laser cutter.  The laboratory is available to faculty, staff and students involved in digital scholarship and object creation.  The Hub is open Monday to Thursday 10:00 a.m to 5 p.m ; Friday 10:00 a.m. to 3:00 pm.  Schedule an appointment with one of our digital scholarship experts, or contact us for more information.    Services          Digital Scholarship Hub  Learn more about the lab, the equipment, installed software, and our digital scholarship team and expertise.             Data Science Tools  Data visualization, text mining, and GIS tools.             Digital Publishing  Digital publishing services offered by the UIC Library, including INDIGO, UIC’s digital repository, Journals@UIC, web publishing tools, and more.             Connect with Experts  Schedule an appointment             Data Management  Data management planning, data curation, data sharing, the DMPTool, and more.             Digital Humanities  The UIC Digital Humanities Initiative is a collaboration between the University Library and the Institute for the Humanities.             Scholarly Communications  Copyright, fair use, open access, and more.        Events  Upcoming Events and Workshops  Resources  The UIC Library provides access to space, equipment, and software to help you create and publish digital scholarship projects.   Technologies  Spaces  Digital Scholarship Hub 1  Digital Scholarship Hub 2  Hardware  Software    Expertise   Data/Text Analysis  Qualitative/Quantitative Analysis  3D Modeling and Rapid Prototyping      INDIGO UIC’s digital repository  Journals@uic.edu Journals published by the UIC Library  DMPtool   Guides  Guides and tutorials on scholarly communication, data, and digital scholarship topics.    ORCID Author Identifiers  Digital Scholarship  Digital Humanities  Indigo  Data Management  Publishing, Scholarly Communication, and Open Access: Overview & Issues  Copyright and Fair Use  OER  Measuring Your Impact: Impact Factor, Citation Analysis, and other Metrics  Selecting Publication Venues: Where to Publish?       How Do I...?     Check out a laptop    Print, scan and copy    Print (Chicago campus)    Use library computers (Chicago campus)     Get More Help      Subject & Course Guides           English 160 &161: Introduction to Library Research           Public Health           Citation and Style Guide Help           Business Research Guide           RefWorks and Other Citation Management Tools           Communication 100           Maps Produced By The U.S. Government           History           Art and Art History           Criminology, Law and Justice      View All Guides          About  Back to content     Events    News    Jobs & Careers     Faculty Support      People     Subject Librarians    Faculty    Staff    Library Departments      Digital Scholarship    Faculty     Projects and Initiatives    Teaching and Learning      Library Policies     User Privacy Policy    Code of Conduct    Service Policy    Col